CatDescriptText: James Whitfield, mill worker, 221 Renfrew Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "Do you believe churches of any denomination receive appreciation financial help from racketeers?" Answer reads: "I don't believe that the churches receive this type of financial help."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of James Whitfield wearing dark leather zippered jacket, plaid polo shirt, moustache, and cap, standing in front of grocery store sign inscribed "cooked salami 55 cents lb old fashioned jumbo 39", brick wall and signs on left
